notes.text: Red Hat Advanced Cluster Management for Kubernetes 2.10.2 is now available.
notes.title: Topic

notes.text:
Red Hat Advanced Cluster Management for Kubernetes 2.10.2 images

Red Hat Advanced Cluster Management for Kubernetes provides the
capabilities to address common challenges that administrators and site
reliability engineers face as they work across a range of public and
private cloud environments. Clusters and applications are all visible and
managed from a single console—with security policy built in.

This advisory contains the container images for Red Hat Advanced Cluster
Management for Kubernetes, which fixes several bugs. See the following
Release Notes documentation, which will be updated shortly for this
release, for additional details about this release:

https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-us/red_hat_advanced_cluster_management_for_kubernetes/2.10/html/release_notes/

Jira issues addressed: 

- ACM-10406: Observability - remove or update addonDeploymentConfig from the clusterManagementAddon is not effect

- ACM-10806: Observability - local-cluster CPU utilization and overestimation data are not display on the Grafana

- ACM-10811: Observability Endpoint in the Hub doesn't reconcile updates to Observability Addon Spec

- ACM-10967: Endless dockercfg secret creation in MCO

- ACM-11008: ACM 2.10 CSV documentation link references v2.9.0 documentation link

- ACM-11071: Observability - Endpoint SA does not get created again in the hub after deletion

cwe.name: Exposure of Sensitive Information to an Unauthorized Actor

notes.text: A vulnerability was found in the follow-redirects package. While processing the cross-domain redirection, `follow-redirects` clears authorization headers, however, it misses clearing proxy-authentication headers, which contain credentials as well. This issue may lead to credential leaking, having a high impact on data confidentiality.
notes.title: Vulnerability description

notes.text: The CVSS score(s) listed for this vulnerability do not reflect the associated product's status, and are included for informational purposes to better understand the severity of this vulnerability.
